We have progress. I have an atypical type of asthma on a base immune cellular level, correlated to my recurrent pneumonia and my EDS. It's also not inflammatory. I Have a new drug starting but this could be quite a long hospital stay as we try and get on top of everything.
So I'm sorry to announce that I am back in the hospital again with another nasty double pneumonia and asthma exacerbation. I have narrowly avoided itu and intubation this time so I'm doing OK.

I'm sad that I had to unfriend someone spouting bollocks that Covid-19 is a hoax. Bloody morons!

Currently I am being told I have now got hospital acquired pneumonia after my usual pneumonia. They are actually trying to kill me what with the highest likely hood that I caught Covid-19 here too. Crazy, crazy.

Update for you all! My doctor says that I have my usual infection and also the Covid-19 thing BUT I am just sleepy and sweaty, on just 3 litres of oxygen (which could easily be dropped to 2 due to how good my o2 sats are) and generally I feel reasonable!

I am not in the least bit shocked after the things I witnessed during this last admission. I'm surprised there aren't more. Nine more confirmed Covid-19 deaths as Northampton General Hospital total passes 100 https://t.co/IhJaHWJZo7

Somebody was able to negotiate an early release 😎 
The doctor agreed with my concerns about Covid-19 and being there. She had me do a walking test for my sats, a blood test to see infection levels/white cell count. So back home, now to get busy with some hardcore resting 🤣

Very unsurprisingly the Covid-19 swab came back as negative. I do not have it. I did expect as much, they expected as much, but I had to follow the procedure and sit on a query ward until I got the all clear. That risk I accept as protocol. #StayHome, avoid any risks.

@Slave2heels I woke up with the indescribable pain thing I have had in my legs occasionally, only this morning it was both of them 😖😫 so I ended up chucking a whole world of opiates and pain meds at them so I could just sit without crying out! So I'm not really with it today!

That feeling when you hug someone and you feel their heart swell and their angst lessen just for a moment. I've given 2 hugs like this today, to 2 ladies I've met who are visiting loved ones who don't have long in this world. Just easing their pain for that moment, priceless.
